sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant T as Transfer Service
    participant R as Redis (idem/limit)
    participant U as User Directory
    participant F as Fraud Engine
    participant A as Account/Ledger Service
    participant DB as Ledger DB (Aurora)
    participant MQ as Event Bus (Kafka)
    participant N as Notification

    C->>GW: POST /transfers (Idempotency-Key, JWT)
    GW->>GW: JWT verify / rate limit
    GW->>T: createTransfer(req)

    T->>R: SETNX idem:{key} = PROCESSING
    alt key exists (duplicate request)
        R-->>T: return existing result
        T-->>C: 200 (same response as before)
    else new request
        R-->>T: OK (lock acquired)
        T->>U: resolve(email/phone) → recipientId
        T->>R: daily/per-txn limit check ($500 / $2,500)
        T->>F: fraud rule evaluation (sync)
        alt high risk
            F-->>T: REVIEW/DENY
            T-->>C: 422 (review required)
        else allow
            F-->>T: ALLOW
            T->>A: executeTransfer(from,to,amount,txnId)
            A->>DB: BEGIN (SERIALIZABLE)
            A->>DB: balance check + double-entry (debit/credit)
            A->>DB: append to ledger_entries (immutable)
            A->>DB: COMMIT
            DB-->>A: OK
            A-->>T: SUCCESS
            T->>R: SET idem:{key} = SUCCESS(result)
            T->>MQ: publish TransferCompleted
            T-->>C: 201 Created (txnId, status=COMPLETED)
            MQ-->>N: notify recipient (Push/SMS)
            MQ-->>A: (async reflection to history service)
        end
    end
